fix_rev.sh is a post commit hook to counter a bug in subversion.
 http://subversion.tigris.org/issues/show_bug.cgi?id=3194

Usage example:

[carlo@mike svn]$ sudo -u svnsync ./fix_rev.sh 
Usage: ./fix_rev.sh <repos> <rev>
[carlo@mike svn]$ sudo -u svnsync ./fix_rev.sh file:///var/svn/anonsvn.jboss.org-jbossas/ 84130
setting svn:date to 2009-02-12T17:02:21.866590Z on 84130
property 'svn:date' set on repository revision 84130
